Today's Progress:

Added a random multi‑brain dialogue feature to the MVP.

The MVP itself was built as a foundation to support the formation of the core ideas. The random multi‑brain dialogue feature I just added is also aimed at a longer‑term direction — where multiple expert brains interact randomly and potentially generate knowledge beyond what we currently know.

The overall design sketch is in docs/random/.

After the first implementation, I was excited. I ran it — and found it wasn't quite what I had hoped for.

They did talk. They did exchange views. But essentially, each expert kept outputting their own direction in every round — it wasn't really a discussion.

So I revised the prompts — emphasized cross‑industry, and the space between different industries. The second version was better than the first, but only marginally.

I revised the prompts again. This time, I made it explicit: each expert should state their own position, then seriously examine whether their direction and the other expert's direction share any unknown intersection. Based on that, they should explore further, push back, and converge.

After this change, the quality of the discussion improved significantly. You can clearly feel that each expert is actively considering whether their own direction and the other's have any overlap — what's missing, what's needed, and how to move forward.

The third version basically achieved the core functionality.

However, the limitations are still obvious:

Prompts are still hard‑coded — and that won't work long‑term. If a valuable direction emerges in round 2 but gets forced into convergence in round 3, that's reverse optimization.

Two experts worked fine. When I added a third, the response time slowed down noticeably.

The director brain's final synthesis — I consider this an experience optimization, not core functionality, so it's lower priority.

Thread pool: still using a single thread pool per call. With only 3 experts, it's fine — but if the system ever scales to more users, it'll need to change.

I haven't yet implemented director brain validation for the discussion's value — that depends heavily on the value system, so I'm leaving it alone for now.

Safety module integration isn't done yet — it involves a different set of design considerations.

...and many more.

